🔹 What is AWS ?

Amazon Web Services (AWS) ek cloud computing platform hai.
👉 Hum bina apna physical server kharide, internet ke through servers, storage, database use kar sakte hain.

Matlab:
Pehle kya hota tha → Company apna data center banati thi 💸
Ab kya hota hai → AWS se rent pe le lo


🔹 What is DataCenter?

Data Center = ek physical building jahan:servers lage hote hain,networking devices hote hain,cooling systems hote hain.

👉 Ye real physical machines hoti hain (virtual nahi)


🔹 What is Region?

Region = ek geographic area jahan AWS apne multiple data centers rakhta hai.

Example:
Mumbai region
US East (Virginia)
Europe (London)

👉 Tum jab AWS use karte ho, tum choose karte ho ki tumhara data kis region mein rahe


🔹What is Availability Zone (AZ)?

AZ = ek region ke andar ka ek isolated data center (ya group of data centers)

👉 Har region ke andar multiple AZs hote hain

Example:

Mumbai region ke andar:
ap-south-1a
ap-south-1b
ap-south-1c

👉 Ye AZs:physically alag hote hain, independent power & network hota hai


Flow:

👉 Data Center → AZ → Region → AWS

Ek AZ mein ek ya multiple data centers
Ek Region mein multiple AZs


Socho:
🏢 Data Center = ek building
🏙️ AZ = ek area jahan multiple buildings hain
🌍 Region = ek city
☁️ AWS = poori duniya ka network


Why multiple AZs?

👉 Agar ek AZ down ho jaye:dusre AZ mein app chalti rahe, high availability milti hai.

Mumbai = 1 Region (multiple AZs ke saath)
Hyderabad = 1 alag Region (apne AZs ke saath)
 
👉 Region = City level
👉 AZ = us city ke andar ke isolated data centers




🔹 1. What is Cloud Computing?

Cloud computing =
👉 Internet ke through IT resources use karna (servers, storage, DB, etc.)

Instead of:
apna server kharidna ❌
maintenance karna ❌

Hum simply:AWS se rent pe lete hain ✅


🔹 2. On-Premise vs Cloud

🏢 On-Premise
Apna data center
High cost 💸
Maintenance khud

☁️ Cloud (AWS)
No hardware
Pay-as-you-go
Scale easily

👉 DevOps mein mostly cloud hi use hota hai

🔹 3. Types of Cloud Services

🔸 IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) 👉 Tumhe server milta hai, baaki sab tum manage karo

Example:
AWS EC2
Tum control karte ho:
OS
software
configs


🔸 PaaS (Platform as a Service) 👉 Platform ready milta hai, tum bas code deploy karo

Example:
AWS Elastic Beanstalk


🔸 SaaS (Software as a Service) 👉 Ready-made software use karo

Examples:
Gmail
Google Docs


🔹 4. Pay-as-you-go Model 👉 Jo use karoge sirf uska paisa doge

Server 1 hour use kiya → 1 hour ka bill
Storage 10GB → utna hi charge

⚠️ Important:
Agar resources band nahi kiye → bill chalta rahega


🔹 5. Scalability vs Elasticity

🔸 Scalability 👉 System ko bada ya chhota karna

Vertical scaling → RAM/CPU badhao, increaseing in the same machine. Example : Increasing size of database
Horizontal scaling → servers add karo, increaing no of machines. Example: Adding one more web servers, to handle web request for application.

🔸 Elasticity 👉 Auto scale based on demand. Deals with adding and removing capactity(resources, memory and disk), whenever it is needed.

Example: EC2,EBS,ECR,ECS,EFS,EKS,etc.
Traffic badha → servers auto add
Traffic kam → servers auto remove


🔹 6. High Availability 👉 System always up rahe

Kaise?
Multiple AZs use karke. Agar ek fail ho:dusra handle kare


🔹 7. Fault Tolerance 👉 System fail hone ke baad bhi kaam kare

Example:
2 servers running
1 crash → dusra still running


🔹 8. Load Balancing 👉 Traffic ko multiple servers mein distribute karna

Example:
1000 users → 4 servers mein divide
👉 Ek server pe load nahi padta


🔹 9. Virtualization 👉 Ek physical server ko multiple virtual servers mein divide karna

Iske bina cloud possible nahi hota
Example:
Ek machine → multiple EC2 instances


🔹 10. Shared Responsibility Model
👉 AWS aur user dono ki responsibility hoti hai

AWS → hardware, data center
Tum → OS, security, data



